# Root cause:
# When flashing multiple LUNs sequentially, the device may leave stale data in the USB
# endpoint buffer from the previous firehose session. When the next LUN's edl.py subprocess
# connects, xmlsend() receives those stale bytes and returns rsp.data=bytes instead of a dict.
# The unguarded 'in rsp.data' dict membership test then raises:
#   TypeError: a bytes-like object is required, not 'str'
# The isinstance(rsp.data, dict) guard short-circuits the check safely when rsp.data is bytes,
# allowing the error path to handle the stale-buffer case without crashing.
#
# Apply with:
#   cd C:\Users\Andrew Price\Desktop\edl-master\edl-master
#   patch -p1 < workspace\patches\firehose_bytes_guard.patch
